His eyes locked onto Kyboah. Just for a moment. Just a fleeting second of eye contact.
And in that moment, Kyboah's will was dominated.
The Khajiit fought. He fought hard. His mind screamed resistance, his hands gripped his sword until his knuckles went white. He focused everything he had on keeping his legs locked in place, refusing to walk, refusing to move toward his friends.
